How to Start a Family Law Case (San Luis Obispo)
body: If you are representing yourself, it is strongly recommended that you attend our workshop so we can:•Explain the stepsto start or respondto a case•Explain how to complete the forms•Explain where to file legal documents•Explain legal termslike legal custody and child support•Explain next steps to finish a case•Review your documents for completeness•Make the necessary copies for filing•Answer general questionsYou do notneed an appointment. Nochildren are allowed. Please bring the following:•Pay stubs for the last 12 months•Account and ownership documents about assets and debts•Tax returns for the last 2 years•Birth certificates of minor children•Marriage certificate

title: How to modify child support, child custody or visitation orders
body: The San Luis Obispo Superior Court Self-Help Center/FamilyLaw Facilitator’sOffice offers a Child Support, Custody and Visitation Workshop to obtain or modify orders.Attendance at this workshop requiresthat you already have a family law or child support case filed with the court.What we can do for you: Provide overview outlining necessary steps to establish or modify child support, custody and/or visitation ordersProvide forms to completeTell you where to file legal documents Explain how to give the documents to the other partyExplain legal terms Help answer general questions You do notneed an appointment to attend the workshop. Nochildren are allowed.
